#Logistics Company Shipment Analysis

This project demonstrates SQL-based analysis of a logistics dataset using joins to answer real-world business questions around customer activity, shipment tracking, and service optimization.

The analysis focuses on connecting customer and shipment data to generate operational and marketing insights.

#Objective

The primary goals of this analysis were to:

-Identify customers who have placed orders
-Track shipments based on delivery status
-Analyze customer shipping behavior
-Identify opportunities for targeted marketing campaigns
-Strengthen SQL skills using joins and filtering logic

#Business Questions

-Which customers have placed an order?
-Which shipments are currently in transit?
-What addresses are associated with active shipments?
-Which customers have not used Express shipping?
-How can joins be used to connect customer and shipment data?
