Analytical Thinking
Methodology
Joined the customers and shipments tables using the shared customer_id field
Used INNER JOIN to combine customer and shipment data
Applied filtering using WHERE to isolate relevant records
Used DISTINCT to remove duplicate customer records
Followed a structured query approach:
Identify relationship → Join tables → Filter results → Interpret insights
Key Insights
Joins enable meaningful connections between customer and operational data
Shipment status filtering provides real-time visibility into logistics operations
Customer segmentation based on shipping method supports targeted marketing
Using DISTINCT ensures clean, non-duplicated customer outputs
Clear column qualification improves query accuracy
Recommendations
Use joins to build operational dashboards for shipment tracking
Monitor in-transit shipments to improve customer communication
Target non-Express customers with promotional campaigns
Continue using structured SQL logic for scalable analysis
