SQL Analysis
1. Customers Who Have Placed an Order
SELECT customers.customer_id,
       customers.customer_name,
       customers.shipping_address
FROM customers
INNER JOIN shipments
    ON customers.customer_id = shipments.customer_id;

Business Insight:
Identifies customers with confirmed shipment activity and links them to delivery locations.

Business Impact:
Supports operational tracking and confirms active customer engagement.

2. Shipments Currently In Transit
SELECT shipments.shipment_id,
       customers.shipping_address
FROM customers
INNER JOIN shipments
    ON customers.customer_id = shipments.customer_id
WHERE shipments.status = 'In Transit';

Business Insight:
Provides visibility into active shipments and their destinations.

Business Impact:
Enables proactive customer communication and operational monitoring.

3. Customers Who Have Not Used Express Shipping
SELECT DISTINCT customers.customer_name,
                customers.contact_email
FROM customers
INNER JOIN shipments
    ON customers.customer_id = shipments.customer_id
WHERE shipments.shipping_method <> 'Express';

Business Insight:
Highlights customers who have not used premium shipping services.

Business Impact:
Supports targeted marketing campaigns to increase Express shipping adoption.

